How to compile & run the program:

-- 1. $ make
This compiles the source code.

-- 2. $ make run dfa=<file path | DFA string codification>
This runs the program with the input value.

[EXAMPLES]

# File input (DFA codification inside)
make run dfa=disconnected_dfa.dfa

Note that *example.dfa* file is included in the src folder and loaded
by default when running (use dfa parameter to specify your own):
$ make run

# String input (be careful with quotation)
$ make run dfa="\"q0 q1 q2 q3; a b; q0; q0 q2; \
  q0 q0 a; q0 q1 b; q1 q1 a; q1 q0 b; q2 q2 a; \
  q2 q3 b; q3 q3 a; q3 q2 b;\""

This DFA is the one given in the example.dfa file.

-- 3. Once all tests are done, don't forget to make clean!
